mechanoreception.notes: Crustaceans generally possess mechanoreceptors for detecting water movement and touch. This is inferred due to their phylogenetic position as crustaceans.

chemoreception.notes: Crustaceans typically use chemoreception to detect chemical cues in the water. This is inferred due to their phylogenetic position as crustaceans.
